-->data types

1]text data types

      string  <class str>

2]sequential

   * list <class list>

      * collection of elements
      * any data type collection (str,int,float,list,tuple)
      * mutable : can modify
      * [] square bracket is represented as list

   * tuple <class tuple>

      * tuple is same as list
      * immutable : can't modify
      * () paranthesis is represented as tuple

3]mapping

   * dictionary <class dict>

      * collection of key value pairs
      * mutable
      * unindexed
      * duplications are not allowed
      * {}
      * eg:{key1 : value1 , key2 : value2 }
4]set

   * set <class set >

      * collection of single elements
      * mutable
      * unindexed
      * duplications are not allowed
      * unordered
      * {}

--> python operators

   * arithemetic

      *  + , - , * , / , % , ** , //
      * eg : 10 / 3 = 3.3333
             10 // 3 = 3
      * % is used to get remainder

   * comparision

      * == , >= , <= , < , > , !=

   * logical

      * and , or ,not
      * eg : a>b and a>c : t and t : true
                         : t and f : false
           : a>b or a>c : t or f : true
                        : f or f : false
     * not(a>b): opposite of user condition

  * assignment

     * = , += , -= , *= , /= , **= , //= , %=
     * eg: a=10
           a+=2 :a= a+2 =12

