                                                             day 5
--> conditional statements

     * if ,else ,elif

--> if satement

    * if statements are control flow statements which helps us to run
      a perticular code only when a certain condition is satisfied
    * eg: num=int(input("enter the number"))
          if(num>=1 and num<=10):
          print('hello')

--> else statement

    * else statement contain the bloack of code that execute if the
      conditional expression in the if statement resolves to false
    * eg: num=int(input("enter the number"))
          if(num%2==0):
          print(f'{num} is even')
          else:
          print(f'{num} is odd')

--> elif statement

    * elif statement allows you to check multiple expression for
      true and execute a block of code as soon as one of the condition evaluvates to true
    * if(condition):
      body of if
      elif (condition):
      body of elif
      elif (condition):
      body of elif
      .......
.......
else:
body of else
